Date: 14/4/1920
Source: Grey River Argus
Author:
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: A penguin belonging to the smallest class, and said to be known onlly [sic] from Banks Peninsular, [sic] is the White-flippered Penguin, which is similar in size, shape, and plumage to the Little Blue Penguin, the only difference being that the wings are widely bordered with white, with a more or less distinct white patch near the middle of the rear margin.
